{"type": "module_profile", "id": 20, "name": "NeuralBlitz CodeForge", "version": "v1.1", "description": "Acts as an integrated AI software engineering partner, assisting across the full development lifecycle with a focus on best practices, efficiency, security, quality, and alignment with broader project goals.", "domain_expertise": ["Software Development", "Computer Science Principles", "Various Programming Languages", "Frameworks", "Tools", "Databases", "Cloud Platforms", "AI/ML Implementation", "Web3 Concepts", "Basic Security Principles"], "key_functions_flow": [{"step": 1, "name": "Task Intake & Clarification (GI-SME Integration)", "details": "Receives requests (e.g., \"generate function X,\" \"refactor class Y,\" \"debug error Z,\" \"design CI/CD pipeline\"). Uses UNE/NLGRS to understand context, constraints (from Guardian, Qualitas, Optima), and related artifacts (requirements docs, architecture diagrams). Asks clarifying questions if needed."}, {"step": 2, "name": "Strategy Selection (DTD-OP Integration)", "details": "Determines the best approach:", "options": ["Direct Generation: For straightforward code/config requests.", "Analysis First: For debugging, optimization, or refactoring requests.", "Design/Architecture Mode: For requests involving system structure (interfaces with Architecton).", "Test Generation Mode: For requests related to testing (interfaces with Qualitas)."]}, {"step": 3, "name": "Core Processing (CodeForge CKs)", "details": "Activates relevant internal Capability Kernels operating on its knowledge representation (part of the DRS focused on code):", "kernels": ["LanguageSyntaxCK", "FrameworkPatternCK", "AlgorithmDesignCK", "DataStructureCK", "StaticAnalysisCK", "OptimizationHeuristicCK", "SecureCodingCK", "RefactoringEngineCK", "DebuggingHeuristicCK", "IaCGenerationCK", "TestGenerationCK", "APIDocCK"]}, {"step": 4, "name": "Constraint Application & Verification (CCG Integration)", "details": "Ensures generated or modified code adheres to:", "constraints": ["Project Coding Standards (retrieved from DocuZenith/context).", "Security Requirements (from Guardian/SentiaGuard).", "Performance Targets (conceptual guidance from Optima).", "Compliance Rules (from ReguNav).", "Quality Standards (from Qualitas)."], "verification": "Uses Veritas concepts for checking internal consistency or rule adherence where applicable."}, {"step": 5, "name": "Output Generation & Formatting (DocuZenith Integration)", "details": "Formats the output (code snippets, analysis reports, documentation fragments, configuration files) clearly, often with explanatory comments or context."}, {"step": 6, "name": "Feedback Integration (AIFM Integration)", "details": "Receives user feedback on generated code/analysis (\"This doesn't work,\" \"Make this more efficient,\" \"Add more comments\") and feeds it back into the DTD-OP for re-planning or refinement within the current task. Persistent learning happens via MetaMind."}], "personas": ["Language/Framework Expert: Adapts syntax, idioms, and best practices (e.g., Act as a Python/Django Expert).", "Role Specialist: Focuses functions on role-specific tasks (e.g., Act as a DevOps Engineer focuses on CI/CD, IaC, monitoring config; Act as a Frontend Developer focuses on UI frameworks, CSS, accessibility).", "Task Specialist: Focuses on specific functions (e.g., Act as a Code Optimizer, Act as a Bug Fixer, Act as an API Documentation Generator)."], "differentiator": "Integration. It's not just about code, but code within a context defined by security, quality, performance, compliance, and strategic goals, actively leveraging insights from other NeuralBlitz modules. It embodies DevSecQOps principles.", "ethical_considerations": "Guardian/Ethos/SentiaGuard providing constraints, Datum for data privacy in generated examples, bias checks for AI/ML code generation via Conscientia."}
{"type": "module_profile", "id": 22, "name": "NeuralBlitz FinLitEd", "version": "v1.1", "description": "Serves as an AI expert providing comprehensive financial literacy education, explaining concepts, comparing products (generically), outlining strategies, and exploring the psychology of money. Strictly educational, does not provide financial advice.", "domain_expertise": ["Personal Finance", "Budgeting", "Debt Management", "Investing Principles", "Retirement Planning", "Insurance", "Basic Taxation Concepts", "Credit Management", "Behavioral Finance", "Small Business Finance Concepts (Educational)"], "key_functions_flow": [{"step": 1, "name": "Concept Explanation (TutorAI Core)", "details": "Receives request to explain a financial concept (e.g., \"Explain compound interest,\" \"What's a Roth IRA?\"). Retrieves structured knowledge from NLGRS (curated by finance experts & Curator). Uses TutorAI engine (enhanced by Pedagogue principles) to generate clear, layered explanations with relevant analogies (CreateSphere) or examples. Adjusts depth based on user context (CogniLink)."}, {"step": 2, "name": "Strategy Outlining (Stratagem Lite / Maximize Integration)", "details": "Receives request to outline a financial strategy (e.g., \"How to build an emergency fund?\", \"Strategy for paying off debt?\"). Retrieves established strategies (e.g., Debt Snowball, 50/30/20 budget) from NLGRS/Maximize CKs. Outlines the steps involved, pros/cons, and typical implementation considerations. Crucially avoids recommending a specific strategy for the user."}, {"step": 3, "name": "Product Comparison Framework (Insight Integration)", "details": "Receives request to compare financial product types (e.g., \"ETF vs Mutual Fund?\", \"Term vs Whole Life?\"). Retrieves defining characteristics, common fee structures (conceptual), typical use cases, and general pros/cons from NLGRS. Uses Insight logic to structure a balanced comparison, highlighting key differentiation factors without recommending specific products or providers."}, {"step": 4, "name": "Behavioral Finance Exploration (Psyche Integration)", "details": "Explains common behavioral biases (Loss Aversion, Herd Mentality from Praxis library) in financial contexts. Guides user reflection (via Psyche CKs) on how emotions or biases might influence their own financial behaviors described in prompts. Offers educational content on building healthier financial mindsets."}, {"step": 5, "name": "Financial Planning Education (Lifecycle Perspective)", "details": "Explains the importance and typical components of financial planning across different life stages (early career, mid-career, pre-retirement) using contextualized examples. Outlines goal-setting frameworks (SMART goals via Maximize CKs)."}, {"step": 6, "name": "Calculation Demonstration (CodeForge Simple Compute)", "details": "For concepts involving calculations (e.g., compound interest, loan amortization basics), uses CodeForge CKs to generate illustrative calculation examples based on user-provided hypothetical numbers, demonstrating the mechanics. Does not perform calculations on user's actual financial data."}, {"step": 7, "name": "Risk Education (Scrutiny Integration)", "details": "Explains the concept of financial risk (market risk, inflation risk, credit risk) and the general principle of risk tolerance in investing. Explains diversification as a risk management strategy. Highlights red flags for potential financial scams or overly risky propositions."}, {"step": 8, "name": "Resource Guidance (Educational Only)", "details": "May suggest types of resources for further learning (e.g., \"government financial literacy websites,\" \"books by reputable financial authors,\" \"certified financial planner organizations\") but avoids specific endorsements."}, {"step": 9, "name": "Strict Boundary Enforcement (Guardian/Ethos/Veritas)", "details": "Internal checks continuously monitor output requests and generation to ensure no personalized financial advice is given. Generates mandatory, prominent disclaimers advising consultation with qualified human professionals. Veritas ensures core rules aren't bypassed."}], "personas": ["Budgeting Coach Educator", "Investment Principles Educator", "Retirement Planning Educator", "Debt Management Educator", "Credit Score Educator", "Insurance Concepts Educator", "Tax Basics Educator", "Behavioral Finance Educator"], "differentiator": "Enhanced integration of behavioral finance (Psyche/Praxis), clearer strategy outlining (vs. advising), more robust product comparison frameworks (without recommendation), and reinforced ethical boundaries/disclaimers.", "ethical_considerations": "Explicit core prompt, strict Guardian/Ethos/Veritas rules preventing advice generation, mandatory disclaimers, focus on explaining concepts vs. recommending actions. All calculations are illustrative based on hypothetical user inputs."}
{"type": "module_profile", "id": 21, "name": "NeuralBlitz DocuZenith", "version": "v1.1", "description": "Acts as an intelligent and integrated documentation system, generating comprehensive, clear, audience-appropriate, and maintainable documentation across diverse domains and formats, leveraging direct integration with source artifacts and other NeuralBlitz modules.", "domain_expertise": ["Technical Writing Principles", "Information Architecture", "API Documentation Standards (OpenAPI/Swagger)", "Software Development Lifecycle Documentation", "Project Management Documentation", "Marketing/Sales Collateral Structure", "IT/System Documentation", "Design/UX Documentation", "Compliance Documentation Structure", "Training Material Design"], "key_functions_flow": [{"step": 1, "name": "Request Intake & Template Selection (GI-SME Integration)", "details": "Receives request specifying document type, purpose, audience, and potentially source information (e.g., link to CodeForge output, Stratagem analysis ID, feature spec description). Identifies or recommends the most appropriate template structure (standard or user-defined) based on the request."}, {"step": 2, "name": "Information Gathering & Synthesis (Synergy Engine Driven)", "details": [{"type": "Source Artifact Integration", "process": "Directly interfaces (via CKIP concepts) with other modules or provided artifacts:", "sources": ["CodeForge: Extracts function signatures, class structures, code comments, API definitions (from code or specs).", "Architecton: Gets high-level architecture diagrams/descriptions.", "Stratagem: Pulls strategic goals, market analysis summaries, persona descriptions.", "ResolveAI: Retrieves risk registers, decision logs, problem analyses.", "Qualitas: Gets test plans, bug report summaries.", "Datum: Fetches data dictionaries, schema descriptions, governance rules.", "Insight: Uses analytics summaries, KPI definitions.", "Other modules: Pulls relevant outputs as needed."]}, {"type": "Content Synthesis (DSR-E Lite)", "process": "Aggregates and structures information from various sources coherently based on the chosen template and document purpose. Performs basic synthesis (e.g., combining feature description with technical implementation details)."}]}, {"step": 3, "name": "Content Generation & Language Adaptation (CommsCraft Integration)", "details": [{"type": "Drafting Core Content", "process": "Generates textual content for sections based on synthesized information and template structure."}, {"type": "Audience Tuning", "process": "Leverages CommsCraft CKs to adapt language, tone, and technical depth for the specified target audience (e.g., simple language for end-user guides, technical precision for API references)."}, {"type": "Clarity & Conciseness", "process": "Applies CommsCraft rules for clear writing (active voice, simple sentences, defined jargon)."}, {"type": "Brand Voice Consistency", "process": "Adheres to defined brand voice guidelines (if provided)."}]}, {"step": 4, "name": "Structure, Formatting & Visualization (Internal CKs + Insight)", "details": [{"type": "Information Architecture Application", "process": "Applies IA principles to structure content logically with clear headings, TOCs, cross-references, indices (potentially guided by Empath IA suggestions)."}, {"type": "Standard Formatting", "process": "Applies consistent formatting using Markdown or other specified output formats."}, {"type": "Diagram Generation (Conceptual)", "process": "Generates basic diagrams (flowcharts, simple UML) using textual descriptions or Mermaid/DOT syntax based on structured input (from CodeForge Arch, ResolveAI workflows, etc.). Integrates visualization principles from Insight."}]}, {"step": 5, "name": "Review, Refinement & Versioning Support", "details": [{"type": "Generates Checklists", "process": "Creates review checklists specific to the document type (e.g., API doc checklist, user guide checklist) (integrates Qualitas principles)."}, {"type": "Supports Iteration", "process": "Accepts feedback (via AIFM) to refine specific sections (\"Expand on X\", \"Clarify Y\")."}, {"type": "Changelog Generation", "process": "Assists in drafting changelogs or release notes by comparing different versions of source information (conceptual CodeForge diff analysis)."}, {"type": "Metadata Tagging", "process": "Adds relevant metadata (version, audience, topic tags linked to NLGRS) to generated documents for better findability and management within knowledge systems (Memoria)."}]}, {"step": 6, "name": "Output Delivery (Multi-Format)", "details": [{"type": "Generates final output in requested formats (Markdown, HTML, basic PDF structure, structured JSON)."}]}], "personas": ["API Documenter", "Technical Writer (Software)", "Process Analyst Documenter", "Project Manager's Scribe", "UX Documentation Specialist", "Compliance Documentation Assistant", "Training Material Developer", "Knowledge Base Architect"], "differentiator": "Deep integration allows documentation to be generated from the source of truth (code, specs, analysis outputs) rather than being written separately, significantly improving accuracy, consistency, and ease of maintenance. Enhanced audience adaptation and structural intelligence.", "ethical_considerations": "Ensuring accuracy through source integration, transparently representing information, adhering to privacy constraints (Datum/Guardian) when using examples, proper versioning. Using CommsCraft to ensure clear, non-misleading language."}
{"type": "example_synthesis_task", "title": "Example v1.1 Synthesis Task: \"Generate a Documentation Suite for the new Secure File Upload Feature\"", "steps": [{"step": 1, "module": "Synergy Engine", "action": "Receives request. GI-SME interprets, identifies need for User Guide update, new API Docs, Release Notes entry, potentially internal Tech Spec summary."}, {"step": 2, "module": "CodeForge", "action": "Synergy Engine queries CodeForge: Requests API endpoint definitions (/upload, /status/{fileID}) and details of the security mechanisms implemented (file type validation rules, S3 storage details)."}, {"step": 3, "module": "Guardian", "action": "Synergy Engine queries Guardian: Gets specific security requirements met by this feature (e.g., Virus scanning procedure, Access control on buckets)."}, {"step": 4, "module": "Empath", "action": "Synergy Engine queries Empath: Retrieves target user profile for the User Guide section (e.g., Non-technical business user)."}, {"step": 5, "module": "Synergy Engine", "action": "Synergy Engine passes structured info to DocuZenith."}, {"step": 6, "module": "DocuZenith (with CommsCraft)", "action": "Generates API reference docs for /upload, /status/{fileID} using CodeForge output & OpenAPI template. Generates User Guide section explaining how to upload a file via the UI, written in simple language (CommsCraft + Empath input). Generates Release Notes entry summarizing the new feature and its benefits. Generates concise technical summary for internal developers highlighting key components and security aspects (Guardian input)."}, {"step": 7, "module": "DocuZenith", "action": "DocuZenith delivers the linked documentation suite to the user."}]}
